@@TJvArrowButton
<GROUP TJvArrowButton>
Summary
  Office style button with arrow. Separated click events for button and arrow.
Description
  The TJvArrowButton control implements a button with a drop down arrow, like the buttons used
  in MicroSoft® Office®. The control has separate click events for the button and the arrow. 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.AllowAllUp
Summary
  Flags if all buttons in a group can be up (depressed).
Description
  AllowAllUp indicates wether or not buttons in the same group all can have the up or depressed
  state. When set to True, all buttons may be in the up state, otherwise at least one button in a
  group must be pressed.
See Also
  Down, GroupIndex
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.ArrowWidth
Summary
  Width of the arrow segment.
Description
  ArrowWidth indicates the width of the arrow segment of the button.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.Down
Summary
  Indicates if the button is down.
Description
  Down indicates wether or not the button is pressed or in it's down state. Setting this property
  to True will set the Down state of all other buttons with the same GroupIndex to False. If
  AllowAllUp = False, you can not set Down to False.
See Also
  AllowAllUp, GroupIndex
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.DropDown
Summary
  Reference to the popup menu associated with the arrow.
Description
  DropDown is a reference to the popup menu to be dropped down when the arrow is clicked. You are
  not required to provide a drop down menu. When the arrow is clicked the OnDrop event is generated
  which allows you to perform a different task.
See Also
  OnDrop
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.FillFont
Summary
  Font used when the mouse is over the control.
Description
  FillFont is the font used to render the caption is while the mouse is over the control.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.Flat
Summary
  Indicates if the button should have flat style.
Description
  Flat indicates if the button should be rendered in a flat style, much like the Flat property of a
  TSpeedButton.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.Glyph
Summary
  The image to show on the button.
Description
  Glyph can be set to a bitmap object containing the image to show on the button. The bitmap can
  contain up to 4 images following the same rules as TSpeedButton.Glyph.
See Also
  NumGlyphs
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.GroupIndex
Summary
  Index of the group this button belongs to.
Description
  GroupIndex holds the index of the group this button is part of. This can be used to simulate radio
  buttons using a group of arrow buttons.

  When the group index of buttons are equal and set to a value <> 0, only 1 button of that group
  is allowed to be left in the down state. Clicking on another button will set that button to the
  down state and release any other button that might be in the down state.
See Also
  AllowAllUp
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.Layout
Summary
  Specifies the location of the image and caption.
Description
  Layout specifies where the image and caption are rendered on the button. See TSpeedButton.Layout
  for more information.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.Margin
Summary
  Space between the border and the image/caption.
Description
  Margin specifies the number of pixels between the button edge and the image or caption. Margin
  works exactly like TSpeedButton.Margin.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.NumGlyphs
Summary
  The number of images in the Glyph property.
Description
  NumGlyphs indicate the number of images the Glyph property holds. NumGlyphs works just like
  TSpeedButton.NumGlyphs.
See Also
  Glyph
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.OnDrop
Summary
  Occurs when the user clicks the arrow.
Description
  Write an OnDrop event to perform special tasks when the user presses the arrow of the button. If a
  DropDown menu is assigned, it will be displayed, regardless if an OnDrop handler is assigned.
See Also
  DropDown
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.PressBoth
Summary
  Specifies if both the button and the arrow should be pressed simultaniously.
Description
  PressBoth indicates wether or not both the button as well as the arrow should be pressed when one
  of the two is clicked. By default this property is set to True.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.Spacing
Summary
  Indicates the position of the image and the caption.
Description
  Spacing specifies the number of pixels between the caption and the image. It works exactly like
  TSpeedButton.Spacing.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

